Class AbstractChunkTimedLoopStartNodeModel

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TimedLoopStart, org.knime.core.node.workflow.LoopStartNode, org.knime.core.node.workflow.LoopStartNodeTerminator, org.knime.core.node.workflow.ScopeStartNode

    public class AbstractChunkTimedLoopStartNodeModel
extends AbstractTimedLoopStartNodeModel

    Extension of the AbstractTimedLoopStartNodeModel class which provides extra settings and method implementations for chunked timed loop start nodes.

    Subclasses should implement RunForTime or RunToTime.

    Author:
    S.Roughley

    • Method Detail

      • getUnprocessedRows

        public org.knime.core.node.BufferedDataTable getUnprocessedRows(org.knime.core.node.ExecutionContext exec)
                                                         throws org.knime.core.node.CanceledExecutionException

        The implementation for chunked loops, returns the unprocessed rows and also provides a progress counter.

        Call this from the Loop end to retrieve unprocessed rows.

        The default implementation returns the unprocessed rows, but is unaware of how many there might be. This should be over-ridden in subclasses if at all possible! Provided for backwards compatibility only.

        Specified by:
        getUnprocessedRows in interface TimedLoopStart
        Overrides:
        getUnprocessedRows in class AbstractTimedLoopStartNodeModel
        Parameters:
        exec - The execution context
        Returns:
        a BufferedDataTable object with the unprocessed rows
        Throws:
        org.knime.core.node.CanceledExecutionException - the canceled execution exception
